        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. War in the Middle East: A sailor stranded in the Gulf fears for his safety Middle East Issued on: 13/03/2026 - 18:03 Modified: 13/03/2026 - 18:11 Since the beginning of the conflict in the Middle East, many merchant vessels have been stranded in the Gulf, as the Strait of Hormuz has become a high-risk area following several attacks attributed to Iran. Among them is Wang Shang, a Chinese sailor aboard a cargo ship, who describes the waiting and uncertainty at sea. As 800,000 flee, half of Lebanon lives in war zones without markets, supplies or healthcare 13/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon’s Mission Impossible: Could US and Israeli pressure to disarm Hezbollah lead to civil war? 13/03/2026 Middle East Strait of Hormuz: Iran leverages control of a critical chokepoint in the global oil trade 13/03/2026 Middle East 'Mental, subjective impact': Iran taking on 'American might' with cyberterrorism 13/03/2026 Middle East Israel widens Lebanon bombing campaign to target north and central Beirut 13/03/2026 On the ground Middle East Netanyahu says new Iran leader 'can't show his face in public' 12/03/2026 Middle East Iran to allow India-flagged tankers to pass through Strait of Hormuz (reports) 12/03/2026 Middle East US Democrats call for 'swift investigation' into strike on Iranian school 12/03/2026 Middle East Middle East war: Dubai targeted by fresh Iranian drone strikes 12/03/2026 Middle East"
